      "writtenOn": "2020-01-03T01:29:48Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I always find the pre- and post- versions of these methods confusing, but basically never would be confused if they were just always the pre- versions\n\n    // faster SkM4{*this, SkM4::Translate(x,y,z)};\n    SkM4 translate(float x, float y, float z) const;\n\n    // faster SkM4{*this, SkM4::Scale(x,y,z)};\n    SkM4 scale(float x, float y, float z) const;\n\nmight want to take a tally through to see if the post- versions really are super valuable?",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 121,
        "startChar": 0,
        "endLine": 132,
        "endChar": 50
      },
      "revId": "613f4c64c24069bd5b9a7ed23cc08a6f0485deec",
