        "id": 5045
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-01-03T01:29:48Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "For concat, since it\u0027s a two-matrix operation, you can really just change the argument order to get the pre- and post- as you like.\n\nSo I\u0027d try even going as far as removing all these methods entirely, either leaning on operator*, the SkM4(const SkM4\u0026, const SkM4\u0026) constructor, SkM4::Concat(), or a concat() method that returns a new SkM4 (with the matrices written in the same order they\u0027d be in math):\n\n    SkM4 concat(const SkM4\u0026 other) const { return SkM4{*this, other}; }\n\nWith that concat() method, \n\n     a.preConcat(b) --\u003e a \u003d a.concat(b)\n    a.postConcat(b) --\u003e a \u003d b.concat(a).",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 134,
        "startChar": 1,
        "endLine": 140,
        "endChar": 5
      },
      "revId": "613f4c64c24069bd5b9a7ed23cc08a6f0485deec",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": true
    },
